classes.name: LazyZipOverHTTP
classes.docstring:
File-like object mapped to a ZIP file over HTTP.

This uses HTTP range requests to lazily fetch the file's content,
which is supposed to be fed to ZipFile.  If such requests are not
supported by the server, raise HTTPRangeRequestUnsupported
during initialization.

methods.name: mode
methods.docstring: Opening mode, which is always rb.

methods.name: seekable
methods.docstring: Return whether random access is supported, which is True.

methods.name: read
methods.docstring:
Read up to size bytes from the object and return them.

As a convenience, if size is unspecified or -1,
all bytes until EOF are returned.  Fewer than
size bytes may be returned if EOF is reached.

methods.name: readable
methods.docstring: Return whether the file is readable, which is True.

methods.name: seek
truncate
methods.docstring:
Resize the stream to the given size in bytes.

If size is unspecified resize to the current position.
The current stream position isn't changed.

Return the new file size.

functions.name: dist_from_wheel_url
functions.docstring:
Return a distribution object from the given wheel URL.

This uses HTTP range requests to only fetch the portion of the wheel
containing metadata, just enough for the object to be constructed.
If such requests are not supported, HTTPRangeRequestUnsupported
is raised.
